* mysqldump -u root -p --databases your_database_name > your_database_name.sql  // Go to your local db and generate the sql scripts for the database using the given command.

* scp your_database_name.sql azureuser@your-vm-ip:/home/azureuser/   // Run the command to copy the .sql file to your Azure VM

* ssh azureuser@your-vm-ip // ssh into the vm

* mysql -u root -p   // login into the mysql

* CREATE DATABASE your_database_name;   //  create the database

* Exit mysql and enter the below command 

* mysql -u root -p your_database_name < /home/azureuser/your_database_name.sql

* Now login to Db and verify the database, tables and table schemas.




